body:
@tahuang1991 is looking into how `CSCCLCTDigi`s in a chamber correlate to the CLCT pre-trigger.  For detailed studies we need to write out the pre-triggers to the ROOT file. He suggested to add the `CSCCLCTPreTriggerDigi` in dataformats. These `CSCCLCTPreTriggerDigi` will not be used anywhere else (neither in the CSC trigger or CSC DAQ code). 

For now `CSCCLCTPreTriggerDigi` is exactly the same as `CSCCLCTDigi`, but in the future we probably want to extend the dataformat with a list of half-strips that participated in the pre-trigger. For this reason we did not want to re-use the `CSCCLCTDigi` object.

I also added a template function in `CSCTriggerPrimitivesBuilder` which removes a lot of code-duplication.

@tahuang1991 @ptcox FYI
